					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Nice work. In the NTSC image, the blue in the trees is clearly a lot darker than in the solid horizontal band of blue.  If the same colour values give very different appearance depending on the surrounding pixels and this is something that developers have taken into account, then the argument for a solution that involves NTSC emulation as opposed to only indexing a fixed palette is pretty solid.  It appears that is the case.
<br />
<br />Will your emulator have a mode which doesn't simulate scanlines?  It looks like yours does it pretty tastefully, but I'd still want to turn them off -- my display is already dimmer than a TV as it is.
<br />Edit: Never mind - I noticed the previous release of Nestopia already has scanline options (including 'none').  Great <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /></div>

